NAME: DEATH AND TAXES

DESCRIPTION: Athletic supplies, class supplies, and a file cabinet were stored in the gym #114 A office staff bathroom and shower. Academic supplies, teaching supplies, and a storage cabinet were also stored in the main modular building staff bathroom #03B. Bathrooms are not clean storage locations. The class items stored in these restrooms could  become a medium of transfer for communicable diseases including norovirus and stomach flu. The storage of these items in these restrooms is an impediment to the cleaning and repair of these facilities and should be removed. Cleaning chemicals, aerosol spray cans, and Clorox wipes must be stored in class areas only accessible to staff and not to students. Examples: Chemical products can be stored in closed or locked cabinets, teacher desk drawers, or supply closets. Student bench that is adjacent to the bus loop has a split and broken board seat. This is a safety hazard due to exposed nail points on the broken seat. The bench should be repaired or replaced A.S.A.P. Recommend cordoning the bench away from student use until repairs are completed.

NAME: THE CARY PUB

DESCRIPTION: Clean kitchen cabinets, counters, sinks, floors, coolers, and equipment of crumbs and residue. Cleaning chemicals and aerosol spray cans on supply cart were left in hallway. Cleaning chemicals and aerosol spray cans must be stored in an area not accessible to students. Example: Store chemicals in a closed and locked stock room. Student personal utensil items sent in daily from their homes must not be placed and washed off in class hand wash sinks. There is potential that these utensils could become contaminated since these hand sinks are for after bathroom use. These personal utensils should be washed off in the kitchen sink and then be sent home daily for cleaning by student families. Student toiletries including a toothbrush were left uncovered in a class bathroom. Personal student items should not be stored in an open bathroom. Toiletries for students should be kept in closed bathroom cabinets and not in contact with other individual student items to prevent cross contamination. School facility sanitation inspection completed.

NAME: Milton's Pizza House

DESCRIPTION: DISCUSSION: Ice machine water supply line had no double check valve backflow preventer. The plumbing system must be protected from backflow of a solid, liquid or gas contaminant at each point of use on food service equipment by installing an approved backflow prevention device (dual check valve) on water supply line (Section 5-203.14 of NC Food Code Manual). Provide double check valve on ice machine water supply line as required.

NAME: La Rancherita

DESCRIPTION: Air conditioning system is nonfunctional in the main gym. The school administration has purchased new roof air conditioning units for the gym and had the installation of these units scheduled for January 17 2022. The installation had to be rescheduled due to winter storm conditions on that date. Management has the installation rescheduled for the next teacher work day in February 2022. This is being done since cranes are being brought on campus on the date of install to lift the air conditioning units on the roof. This work needs to be completed when students are not present on campus. A follow up visit will be conducted by this department after installation is completed to verify that the gym air conditioning system is functional. Repair nonfunctional ceiling light fixtures in classroom #4. Replace changing pad with torn covering on diapering station in the shared bathroom in preschool building #1. Diaper changing pads must have intact water proof surfaces to allow for proper cleaning and disinfection between student uses. Replace splintered and damaged wooden components on the play tunnel in front of building #3. Replace loose roof boards on bike shelters along the toddler playground loop.

DISCUSSION: If meatballs and sauce are being heated for the first time out of package, the final reheat temperature has to be at least 135F throughout product. If meatballs and sauce were reheated and cooled in restaurant, the next time they are heated, they must be reheated to 165F or above throughout entire product before placing on preheated steam table. Always use calibrated metal stemmed food thermometer to check food temperatures--not a surface temperature reading infrared thermometer.

DESCRIPTION: Replace missing seat on see saw playground structure. (Priority safety repair. Please repair A.S.A.P.) Cleaning chemicals including Clorox and Lysol wipes and aerosol sprays should be stored in areas only accessible to staff and should not be left in areas accessible to students. Example: These chemical products can be stored in closed or locked cabinets. Emergency changes of clothing for students in the elementary school health room bathroom should be kept in a covered container to protect the clothing from possible sources of contamination. Examples: The changes of clothing could be kept in a closed cabinet or in plastic bins with lids. Facility sanitation inspection of elementary and middle school facilities completed.
